      <hedline>
        <hl1>Control Yourself</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rene Carrillo letter recalls when flight attendant on Continental flight from Savannah, Ga, announced that toilets were not working and that passengers should 'hold it until we get to Newark' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Travel section receives hundreds of letters from readers about their experiences with airline travel. Although most write to complain, a small number actually offer words of praise. Here is a selection from the last year:</p>
        <p>To the Editor: On my two-and-a-half-hour Continental flight from Savannah, Ga., to Newark, the flight attendant made the following announcement: ''The toilets are not operational. If you must use the toilets, hold it until we get to Newark.''</p>
        <p>RENE CARRILLO  Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
